# Sahayogi

Sahayogi is a Flask, Jinja, and MySQL student project for a skill exchange product.

The implementation is intentionally scoped:

- Active backend: registration, login/logout needed for access, role access, and admin dashboard/user role management.
- Frontend-only surfaces: listings, profile editing, credits, matches, requests, exchanges, messages, notifications, reviews, reports, certificates, categories, and skills.

The frontend-only pages keep the existing templates and navigation, but they do not create, update, delete, or settle backend records.

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- MySQL Server 8.x or 9.x
- MySQL Workbench
- Visual Studio Code

## Quick Setup

Run from the project root:

```powershell
py setup.py
```

The setup script will:

1. Find MySQL.
2. Prompt for the MySQL root password.
3. Create `sahayogi` and `sahayogi_test`.
4. Create `venv`.
5. Install Python dependencies.
6. Generate `.env`.
7. Ask whether to configure Gmail SMTP or log email locally.
8. Create the guide-defined MySQL tables.
9. Seed roles and the default admin account.

Start the app:

```powershell
py run.py
```

Open `http://localhost:5000`.

## Default Admin

| Role | Email | Password |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Admin | `admin@example.com` | `Admin123!` |

## Manual Setup

```powershell
py -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create `.env` from `.env.example`, then create the databases:

```sql
CREATE DATABASE sahayogi CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE DATABASE sahayogi_test CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
```

Create tables and seed active backend reference data:

```powershell
.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run init-db
.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run seed-reference-data
```

## Commands

| Command | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `py setup.py` | Full first-time setup |
| `py run.py` | Start the app, auto-using `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe` when available |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run init-db` | Create the guide-defined MySQL tables |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run seed-reference-data` | Seed roles and default admin |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run seed-demo-data` | No-op placeholder; demo listing/exchange backend is out of scope |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run elevate-user <email>` | Promote a registered user to admin |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run test-email you@example.com` | Send or locally log a test email |
| `Get-Content -Tail 40 instance\mail.log` | Show locally captured emails |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -q` | Run the reduced backend test suite |

