## Active Backend Rules

Registration validates required fields, hashes passwords, assigns the `user` role, creates a profile shell, and sends or logs email verification.

Role access uses `admin_required` on admin routes. Admins can promote or demote users between `user` and `admin`, and role changes are audit logged.

The admin dashboard reads only active backend tables: users, roles, profiles, and admin audit logs.
